   1799, 'https://www.kentuckyhauntedhouses.com/real-haunt/white-hall.html'),

  ('camp-nelson', 'Camp Nelson National Monument', 'Nicholasville', '6614 Danville Road', 'KY', 37.7886, -84.5986, 'battlefield',
   'Established in 1863 as a Union Army supply depot, Camp Nelson became one of the largest recruitment and training centers for African American soldiers. It also served as a refugee camp for the families of enslaved men who joined the army.',
   'Park rangers have seen apparitions of an African American family in Civil War-era clothing who vanished before their eyes. The hardships faced by the refugee families - hunger, disease, and exposure - left spiritual imprints on the land. Visitors report unexplained phenomena connected to the site''s role in the struggle for freedom.',
   1863, 'https://maplehillmanor.com/blog/2025/03/haunted-places-in-kentucky/'),

  ('colville-covered-bridge', 'Colville Covered Bridge', 'Millersburg', 'Colville Road', 'KY', 38.2894, -84.1500, 'other',
   'Built in 1877 by Jacob Bower, this picturesque 124-foot covered bridge over Hinkston Creek is one of Kentucky''s few remaining historic covered bridges. Its rural setting and age have made it the subject of numerous ghost stories.',
   'Strange shadows are seen inside the bridge at night, and lights shine up through the floorboards as if from headlights submerged in the water below. Drivers report seeing phantom headlights in their rearview mirrors that vanish as if a ghostly car veered into the creek. The Bluegrass Ghost Chasers investigated and captured an unfamiliar laugh on their recorders. Urban legends speak of hangings and decapitations at the bridge.',
   1877, 'https://fox56news.com/news/spirit-of-bluegrass/ghost-stories-linked-to-kentucky-covered-bridge/');

